  "text": "One who bakes [something] the size of a dried fig is liable. It is the same whether he bakes bread, cooks a food or herbs or heats up water – it all has one function. The [requisite] amount of heating water is enough to bathe a small limb. And the [requisite] amount of cooking herbs is enough that they be fit for the purpose for which they are being cooked.",
